fcFabricName.name: fcFabricName
fcFabricName.description: The Name_Identifier of the Fabric to which this Fabric Element belongs.

fcElementName.name: fcElementName
fcElementName.description: The Name_Identifier of the Fabric Element.

fcFeModuleCapacity.name: fcFeModuleCapacity
fcFeModuleCapacity.description: The maximum number of modules in the Fabric Element, regardless of their current state.

fcFeModuleTable.name: fcFeModuleTable
fcFeModuleTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each module in the Fabric Element, information of the modules.

fcFeModuleEntry.name: fcFeModuleEntry
fcFeModuleEntry.description: An entry containing the configuration parameters of a module.

fcFeModuleIndex.name: fcFeModuleIndex
fcFeModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module within the Fabric Element for which this entry contains information. This value is never greater than fcFeModuleCapacity.

fcFeModuleDescr.name: fcFeModuleDescr
fcFeModuleDescr.description: A textual description of the module. This value should include the full name and version identification of the module. It should contain printable ASCII characters.

fcFeModuleObjectID.name: fcFeModuleObjectID
fcFeModuleObjectID.description: The vendor's authoritative identification of the module. This value may be allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides a straight-forward and unambiguous means for determining what kind of module is being managed. For example, this object could take the value 1.3.6.1.4.1.99649.3.9 if vendor 'Neufe Inc.' was assigned the subtree 1.3.6.1.4.1.99649, and had assigned the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.99649.3.9 to its 'FeFiFo-16 PlugInCard.'

fcFeModuleOperStatus.name: fcFeModuleOperStatus
fcFeModuleOperStatus.description: This object indicates the operational status of the module: online(1) the module is functioning properly; offline(2) the module is not available; testing(3) the module is under testing; and faulty(4) the module is defective in some way.

fcFeModuleLastChange.name: fcFeModuleLastChange
fcFeModuleLastChange.description: This object contains the value of sysUpTime when the module entered its current operational status. A value of zero indicates that the operational status of the module has not changed since the agent last restarted.

fcFeModuleFxPortCapacity.name: fcFeModuleFxPortCapacity
fcFeModuleFxPortCapacity.description: The number of FxPort that can be contained within the module. Within each module, the ports are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to fcFeModuleFxPortCapacity inclusive. However, the numbers are not required to be contiguous.

fcFxConfTable.name: fcFxConfTable
fcFxConfTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, configuration and service parameters of the FxPorts.

fcFxConfEntry.name: fcFxConfEntry
fcFxConfEntry.description: An entry containing the configuration and service parameters of a FxPort.

fcFxConfModuleIndex.name: fcFxConfModuleIndex
fcFxConfModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxConfFxPortIndex.name: fcFxConfFxPortIndex
fcFxConfFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortName.name: fcFxPortName
fcFxPortName.description: The name identifier of this FxPort. Each FxPort has a unique port name within the address space of the Fabric.

fcFxPortFcphVersionHigh.name: fcFxPortFcphVersionHigh
fcFxPortFcphVersionHigh.description: The highest or most recent version of FC-PH that the FxPort is configured to support.

fcFxPortFcphVersionLow.name: fcFxPortFcphVersionLow
fcFxPortFcphVersionLow.description: The lowest or earliest version of FC-PH that the FxPort is configured to support.

fcFxPortBbCredit.name: fcFxPortBbCredit
fcFxPortBbCredit.description: The total number of receive buffers available for holding Class 1 connect-request, Class 2 or 3 frames from the attached NxPort. It is for buffer-to-buffer flow control in the direction from the attached NxPort (if applicable) to FxPort.

fcFxPortRxBufSize.name: fcFxPortRxBufSize
fcFxPortRxBufSize.description: The largest Data_Field Size (in octets) for an FT_1 frame that can be received by the FxPort.

fcFxPortRatov.name: fcFxPortRatov
fcFxPortRatov.description: The Resource_Allocation_Timeout Value configured for the FxPort. This is used as the timeout value for determining when to reuse an NxPort resource such as a Recovery_Qualifier. It represents E_D_TOV (see next object) plus twice the maximum time that a frame may be delayed within the Fabric and still be delivered.

fcFxPortEdtov.name: fcFxPortEdtov
fcFxPortEdtov.description: The E_D_TOV value configured for the FxPort. The Error_Detect_Timeout Value is used as the timeout value for detecting an error condition.

fcFxPortCosSupported.name: fcFxPortCosSupported
fcFxPortCosSupported.description: A value indicating the set of Classes of Service supported by the FxPort.

fcFxPortIntermixSupported.name: fcFxPortIntermixSupported
fcFxPortIntermixSupported.description: A flag indicating whether or not the FxPort supports an Intermixed Dedicated Connection.

fcFxPortStackedConnMode.name: fcFxPortStackedConnMode
fcFxPortStackedConnMode.description: A value indicating the mode of Stacked Connect supported by the FxPort.

fcFxPortClass2SeqDeliv.name: fcFxPortClass2SeqDeliv
fcFxPortClass2SeqDeliv.description: A flag indicating whether or not Class 2 Sequential Delivery is supported by the FxPort.

fcFxPortClass3SeqDeliv.name: fcFxPortClass3SeqDeliv
fcFxPortClass3SeqDeliv.description: A flag indicating whether or not Class 3 Sequential Delivery is supported by the FxPort.

fcFxPortHoldTime.name: fcFxPortHoldTime
fcFxPortHoldTime.description: The maximum time (in microseconds) that the FxPort shall hold a frame before discarding the frame if it is unable to deliver the frame. The value 0 means that the FxPort does not support this parameter.

fcFxPortBaudRate.name: fcFxPortBaudRate
fcFxPortBaudRate.description: The FC-0 baud rate of the FxPort.

fcFxPortMedium.name: fcFxPortMedium
fcFxPortMedium.description: The FC-0 medium of the FxPort.

fcFxPortTxType.name: fcFxPortTxType
fcFxPortTxType.description: The FC-0 transmitter type of the FxPort.

fcFxPortDistance.name: fcFxPortDistance
fcFxPortDistance.description: The FC-0 distance range of the FxPort transmitter.

fcFxPortOperTable.name: fcFxPortOperTable
fcFxPortOperTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, operational status and parameters of the FxPorts.

fcFxPortOperEntry.name: fcFxPortOperEntry
fcFxPortOperEntry.description: An entry containing operational status and parameters of a FxPort.

fcFxPortOperModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortOperModuleIndex
fcFxPortOperModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortOperFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortOperFxPortIndex
fcFxPortOperFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortID.name: fcFxPortID
fcFxPortID.description: The address identifier by which this FxPort is identified within the Fabric. The FxPort may assign its address identifier to its attached NxPort(s) during Fabric Login.

fcFPortAttachedPortName.name: fcFPortAttachedPortName
fcFPortAttachedPortName.description: The port name of the attached N_Port, if applicable. If the value of this object is '0000000000000000'H, this FxPort has no NxPort attached to it. This variable has been deprecated and may be implemented for backward compability.

fcFPortConnectedPort.name: fcFPortConnectedPort
fcFPortConnectedPort.description: The address identifier of the destination FxPort with which this FxPort is currently engaged in a either a Class 1 or loop connection. If the value of this object is '000000'H, this FxPort is not engaged in a connection. This variable has been deprecated and may be implemented for backward compability.

fcFxPortBbCreditAvailable.name: fcFxPortBbCreditAvailable
fcFxPortBbCreditAvailable.description: The number of buffers currently available for receiving frames from the attached port in the buffer-to-buffer flow control. The value should be less than or equal to fcFxPortBbCredit.

fcFxPortOperMode.name: fcFxPortOperMode
fcFxPortOperMode.description: The current operational mode of the FxPort.

fcFxPortAdminMode.name: fcFxPortAdminMode
fcFxPortAdminMode.description: The desired operational mode of the FxPort.

fcFxPortPhysTable.name: fcFxPortPhysTable
fcFxPortPhysTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, physical level status and parameters of the FxPorts.

fcFxPortPhysEntry.name: fcFxPortPhysEntry
fcFxPortPhysEntry.description: An entry containing physical level status and parameters of a FxPort.

fcFxPortPhysModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortPhysModuleIndex
fcFxPortPhysModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortPhysFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortPhysFxPortIndex
fcFxPortPhysFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus.name: fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus
fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the FxPort. A management station may place the FxPort in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational frames can be passed. When a Fabric Element initializes, all FxPorts start with fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus in the offline(2) state. As the result of either explicit management action or per configuration information accessible by the Fabric Element, fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus is then changed to either the online(1) or testing(3) states, or remains in the offline state.

fcFxPortPhysOperStatus.name: fcFxPortPhysOperStatus
fcFxPortPhysOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the FxPort. The testing(3) indicates that no operational frames can be passed. If fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus is offline(2) then fcFxPortPhysOperStatus should be offline(2). If fcFxPortPhysAdminStatus is changed to online(1) then fcFxPortPhysOperStatus should change to online(1) if the FxPort is ready to accept Fabric Login request from the attached NxPort; it should proceed and remain in the link-failure(4) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents it from going to the online(1) state.

fcFxPortPhysLastChange.name: fcFxPortPhysLastChange
fcFxPortPhysLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the FxPort entered its current operational status. A value of zero indicates that the FxPort's operational status has not changed since the agent last restarted.

fcFxPortPhysRttov.name: fcFxPortPhysRttov
fcFxPortPhysRttov.description: The Receiver_Transmitter_Timeout value of the FxPort. This is used by the receiver logic to detect Loss of Synchronization.

fcFxlogiTable.name: fcFxlogiTable
fcFxlogiTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, services parameters established from the most recent Fabric Login, explicit or implicit.

fcFxlogiEntry.name: fcFxlogiEntry
fcFxlogiEntry.description: An entry containing service parameters established from a successful Fabric Login.

fcFxlogiModuleIndex.name: fcFxlogiModuleIndex
fcFxlogiModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxlogiFxPortIndex.name: fcFxlogiFxPortIndex
fcFxlogiFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxlogiNxPortIndex.name: fcFxlogiNxPortIndex
fcFxlogiNxPortIndex.description: The object identifies the associated NxPort in the attachment for which the entry contains information.

fcFxPortFcphVersionAgreed.name: fcFxPortFcphVersionAgreed
fcFxPortFcphVersionAgreed.description: The version of FC-PH that the FxPort has agreed to support from the Fabric Login

fcFxPortNxPortBbCredit.name: fcFxPortNxPortBbCredit
fcFxPortNxPortBbCredit.description: The total number of buffers available for holding Class 1 connect-request, Class 2 or Class 3 frames to be transmitted to the attached NxPort. It is for buffer- to-buffer flow control in the direction from FxPort to NxPort. The buffer-to-buffer flow control mechanism is indicated in the respective fcFxPortBbCreditModel. [1](23.6.2.2)

fcFxPortNxPortRxDataFieldSize.name: fcFxPortNxPortRxDataFieldSize
fcFxPortNxPortRxDataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size of the attached NxPort. This is a binary value that specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame that can be received by the NxPort. The value is in number of bytes and ranges from 128 to 2112 inclusive.

fcFxPortCosSuppAgreed.name: fcFxPortCosSuppAgreed
fcFxPortCosSuppAgreed.description: A variable indicating that the attached NxPort has requested the FxPort for the support of classes of services and the FxPort has granted the request.

fcFxPortIntermixSuppAgreed.name: fcFxPortIntermixSuppAgreed
fcFxPortIntermixSuppAgreed.description: A variable indicating that the attached NxPort has requested the FxPort for the support of Intermix and the FxPort has granted the request. This flag is only valid if Class 1 service is supported.

fcFxPortStackedConnModeAgreed.name: fcFxPortStackedConnModeAgreed
fcFxPortStackedConnModeAgreed.description: A variable indicating whether the FxPort has agreed to support stacked connect from the Fabric Login. This is only meaningful if Class 1 service has been agreed.

fcFxPortClass2SeqDelivAgreed.name: fcFxPortClass2SeqDelivAgreed
fcFxPortClass2SeqDelivAgreed.description: A variable indicating whether the FxPort has agreed to support Class 2 sequential delivery from the Fabric Login. This is only meaningful if Class 2 service has been agreed.

fcFxPortClass3SeqDelivAgreed.name: fcFxPortClass3SeqDelivAgreed
fcFxPortClass3SeqDelivAgreed.description: A flag indicating whether the FxPort has agreed to support Class 3 sequential delivery from the Fabric Login. This is only meaningful if Class 3 service has been agreed.

fcFxPortNxPortName.name: fcFxPortNxPortName
fcFxPortNxPortName.description: The port name of the attached NxPort, if applicable. If the value of this object is '0000000000000000'H, this FxPort has no NxPort attached to it.

fcFxPortConnectedNxPort.name: fcFxPortConnectedNxPort
fcFxPortConnectedNxPort.description: The address identifier of the destination FxPort with which this FxPort is currently engaged in a either a Class 1 or loop connection. If the value of this object is '000000'H, this FxPort is not engaged in a connection.

fcFxPortBbCreditModel.name: fcFxPortBbCreditModel
fcFxPortBbCreditModel.description: This object identifies the BB_Credit model used by the FxPort. The regular model refers to the Buffer-to-Buffer flow control mechanism defined in FC-PH [1] is used between the F_Port and the N_Port. For FL_Ports, the Alternate Buffer-to-Buffer flow control mechanism as defined in FC-AL [4] is used between the FL_Port and any attached NL_Ports.

fcFxPortErrorTable.name: fcFxPortErrorTable
fcFxPortErrorTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort, counters that record the numbers of errors detected.

fcFxPortErrorEntry.name: fcFxPortErrorEntry
fcFxPortErrorEntry.description: An entry containing error counters of a FxPort.

fcFxPortErrorModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortErrorModuleIndex
fcFxPortErrorModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortErrorFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortErrorFxPortIndex
fcFxPortErrorFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortLinkFailures.name: fcFxPortLinkFailures
fcFxPortLinkFailures.description: The number of link failures detected by this FxPort.

fcFxPortSyncLosses.name: fcFxPortSyncLosses
fcFxPortSyncLosses.description: The number of loss of synchronization detected by the FxPort.

fcFxPortSigLosses.name: fcFxPortSigLosses
fcFxPortSigLosses.description: The number of loss of signal detected by the FxPort.

fcFxPortPrimSeqProtoErrors.name: fcFxPortPrimSeqProtoErrors
fcFxPortPrimSeqProtoErrors.description: The number of primitive sequence protocol errors detected by the FxPort.

fcFxPortInvalidTxWords.name: fcFxPortInvalidTxWords
fcFxPortInvalidTxWords.description: The number of invalid transmission word detected by the FxPort.

fcFxPortInvalidCrcs.name: fcFxPortInvalidCrcs
fcFxPortInvalidCrcs.description: The number of invalid CRC detected by this FxPort.

fcFxPortDelimiterErrors.name: fcFxPortDelimiterErrors
fcFxPortDelimiterErrors.description: The number of Delimiter Errors detected by this FxPort.

fcFxPortAddressIdErrors.name: fcFxPortAddressIdErrors
fcFxPortAddressIdErrors.description: The number of address identifier errors detected by this FxPort.

fcFxPortLinkResetIns.name: fcFxPortLinkResetIns
fcFxPortLinkResetIns.description: The number of Link Reset Protocol received by this FxPort from the attached NxPort.

fcFxPortLinkResetOuts.name: fcFxPortLinkResetOuts
fcFxPortLinkResetOuts.description: The number of Link Reset Protocol issued by this FxPort to the attached NxPort.

fcFxPortOlsIns.name: fcFxPortOlsIns
fcFxPortOlsIns.description: The number of Offline Sequence received by this FxPort.

fcFxPortOlsOuts.name: fcFxPortOlsOuts
fcFxPortOlsOuts.description: The number of Offline Sequence issued by this FxPort.

fcFxPortC1AcctTable.name: fcFxPortC1AcctTable
fcFxPortC1AcctTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, Class 1 accounting information recorded since the management agent has re-initialized.

fcFxPortC1AcctEntry.name: fcFxPortC1AcctEntry
fcFxPortC1AcctEntry.description: An entry containing Class 1 accounting information for each FxPort.

fcFxPortC1AcctModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortC1AcctModuleIndex
fcFxPortC1AcctModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortC1AcctFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortC1AcctFxPortIndex
fcFxPortC1AcctFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortC1InConnections.name: fcFxPortC1InConnections
fcFxPortC1InConnections.description: The number of Class 1 connections successfully established in which the attached NxPort is the source of the connect-request.

fcFxPortC1OutConnections.name: fcFxPortC1OutConnections
fcFxPortC1OutConnections.description: The number of Class 1 connections successfully established in which the attached NxPort is the destination of the connect-request.

fcFxPortC1FbsyFrames.name: fcFxPortC1FbsyFrames
fcFxPortC1FbsyFrames.description: The number of F_BSY frames generated by this FxPort against Class 1 connect-request.

fcFxPortC1FrjtFrames.name: fcFxPortC1FrjtFrames
fcFxPortC1FrjtFrames.description: The number of F_RJT frames generated by this FxPort against Class 1 connect-request.

fcFxPortC1ConnTime.name: fcFxPortC1ConnTime
fcFxPortC1ConnTime.description: The cumulative time that this FxPort has been engaged in Class 1 connection. The amount of time of each connection is counted in octets from after a connect- request has been accepted until the connection is disengaged, either by an EOFdt or Link Reset.

fcFxPortC1InFrames.name: fcFxPortC1InFrames
fcFxPortC1InFrames.description: The number of Class 1 frames (other than Class 1 connect-request) received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC1OutFrames.name: fcFxPortC1OutFrames
fcFxPortC1OutFrames.description: The number of Class 1 frames (other than Class 1 connect-request) delivered through this FxPort to its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC1InOctets.name: fcFxPortC1InOctets
fcFxPortC1InOctets.description: The number of Class 1 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC1OutOctets.name: fcFxPortC1OutOctets
fcFxPortC1OutOctets.description: The number of Class 1 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, delivered through this FxPort its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC1Discards.name: fcFxPortC1Discards
fcFxPortC1Discards.description: The number of Class 1 frames discarded by this FxPort.

fcFxPortC2AcctTable.name: fcFxPortC2AcctTable
fcFxPortC2AcctTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, Class 2 accounting information recorded since the management agent has re-initialized.

fcFxPortC2AcctEntry.name: fcFxPortC2AcctEntry
fcFxPortC2AcctEntry.description: An entry containing Class 2 accounting information for each FxPort.

fcFxPortC2AcctModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortC2AcctModuleIndex
fcFxPortC2AcctModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortC2AcctFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortC2AcctFxPortIndex
fcFxPortC2AcctFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortC2InFrames.name: fcFxPortC2InFrames
fcFxPortC2InFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC2OutFrames.name: fcFxPortC2OutFrames
fcFxPortC2OutFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames delivered through this FxPort to its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC2InOctets.name: fcFxPortC2InOctets
fcFxPortC2InOctets.description: The number of Class 2 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC2OutOctets.name: fcFxPortC2OutOctets
fcFxPortC2OutOctets.description: The number of Class 2 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, delivered through this FxPort to its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC2Discards.name: fcFxPortC2Discards
fcFxPortC2Discards.description: The number of Class 2 frames discarded by this FxPort.

fcFxPortC2FbsyFrames.name: fcFxPortC2FbsyFrames
fcFxPortC2FbsyFrames.description: The number of F_BSY frames generated by this FxPort against Class 2 frames.

fcFxPortC2FrjtFrames.name: fcFxPortC2FrjtFrames
fcFxPortC2FrjtFrames.description: The number of F_RJT frames generated by this FxPort against Class 2 frames.

fcFxPortC3AcctTable.name: fcFxPortC3AcctTable
fcFxPortC3AcctTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort in the Fabric Element, Class 3 accounting information recorded since the management agent has re-initialized.

fcFxPortC3AcctEntry.name: fcFxPortC3AcctEntry
fcFxPortC3AcctEntry.description: An entry containing Class 3 accounting information for each FxPort.

fcFxPortC3AcctModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortC3AcctModuleIndex
fcFxPortC3AcctModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortC3AcctFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortC3AcctFxPortIndex
fcFxPortC3AcctFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortC3InFrames.name: fcFxPortC3InFrames
fcFxPortC3InFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC3OutFrames.name: fcFxPortC3OutFrames
fcFxPortC3OutFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames delivered through this FxPort to its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC3InOctets.name: fcFxPortC3InOctets
fcFxPortC3InOctets.description: The number of Class 3 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, received by this FxPort from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC3OutOctets.name: fcFxPortC3OutOctets
fcFxPortC3OutOctets.description: The number of Class 3 frame octets, including the frame delimiters, delivered through this FxPort to its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortC3Discards.name: fcFxPortC3Discards
fcFxPortC3Discards.description: The number of Class 3 frames discarded by this FxPort.

fcFxPortCapTable.name: fcFxPortCapTable
fcFxPortCapTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each FxPort, the capabilities of the port within the Fabric Element.

fcFxPortCapEntry.name: fcFxPortCapEntry
fcFxPortCapEntry.description: An entry containing the capabilities of a FxPort.

fcFxPortCapModuleIndex.name: fcFxPortCapModuleIndex
fcFxPortCapModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module containing the FxPort for which this entry contains information.

fcFxPortCapFxPortIndex.name: fcFxPortCapFxPortIndex
fcFxPortCapFxPortIndex.description: This object identifies the FxPort within the module. This number ranges from 1 to the value of fcFeModulePortCapacity for the associated module. The value remains constant for the identified FxPort until the module is re-initialized.

fcFxPortCapFcphVersionHigh.name: fcFxPortCapFcphVersionHigh
fcFxPortCapFcphVersionHigh.description: The highest or most recent version of FC-PH that the FxPort is capable of supporting.

fcFxPortCapFcphVersionLow.name: fcFxPortCapFcphVersionLow
fcFxPortCapFcphVersionLow.description: The lowest or earliest version of FC-PH that the FxPort is capable of supporting.

fcFxPortCapBbCreditMax.name: fcFxPortCapBbCreditMax
fcFxPortCapBbCreditMax.description: The maximum number of receive buffers available for holding Class 1 connect-request, Class 2 or Class 3 frames from the attached NxPort.

fcFxPortCapBbCreditMin.name: fcFxPortCapBbCreditMin
fcFxPortCapBbCreditMin.description: The minimum number of receive buffers available for holding Class 1 connect-request, Class 2 or Class 3 frames from the attached NxPort.

fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMax.name: fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMax
fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMax.description: The maximum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that the FxPort is capable of receiving from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMin.name: fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMin
fcFxPortCapRxDataFieldSizeMin.description: The minimum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that the FxPort is capable of receiving from its attached NxPort.

fcFxPortCapCos.name: fcFxPortCapCos
fcFxPortCapCos.description: A value indicating the set of Classes of Service that the FxPort is capable of supporting.

fcFxPortCapIntermix.name: fcFxPortCapIntermix
